00:35:08.020 --> 00:35:11.280
So they have this small kind
of a piece of a-- like a lid.

00:35:11.280 --> 00:35:14.720
You know the lids which come out
of the tuna box and everything

00:35:14.720 --> 00:35:17.200
So that kind of little
finger handle, and then

00:35:17.200 --> 00:35:19.070
she had made holes in it.

00:35:19.070 --> 00:35:21.730
So what she would do that
she wants to slide over

00:35:21.730 --> 00:35:24.980
that little block of
potato starch block,

00:35:24.980 --> 00:35:26.812
and the noodles will come out.

00:35:26.812 --> 00:35:27.520
It's in the book.

00:35:27.520 --> 00:35:29.840
And I'm looking at
this, and I was, like,

00:35:29.840 --> 00:35:32.520
wow, that is fantastic.

00:35:32.520 --> 00:35:34.262
So what she does is
that she makes them

00:35:34.262 --> 00:35:36.470
