00:38:03.350 --> 00:38:07.480
There was a Tibetan woman
from the top of the hill.

00:38:07.480 --> 00:38:11.514
She ran down the slope to
give my computer back to me.

00:38:11.514 --> 00:38:12.756
IRFAN DAMA: Wow.

00:38:12.756 --> 00:38:13.819
Incredible.

00:38:13.819 --> 00:38:16.360
VIKAS KHANNA: And I'm trying to
give her something, because I

00:38:16.360 --> 00:38:17.693
don't know how to react to this.

00:38:17.693 --> 00:38:21.950
Like nobody has done this
kind of running for me.

00:38:21.950 --> 00:38:24.420
So she shrugged, and she
said something in Tibetan.

00:38:24.420 --> 00:38:25.970
I asked the driver.

00:38:25.970 --> 00:38:28.250
She said that anyone
would have done that.

00:38:28.250 --> 00:38:30.050
IRFAN DAMA: Wow.

00:38:30.050 --> 00:38:33.192
VIKAS KHANNA: And she must
have that ran about two miles,

00:38:33.192 --> 00:38:35.410
more than that.

00:38:35.410 --> 00:38:38.440
And that sight never leaves me.

00:38:38.440 --> 00:38:41.100
You know, the married women
wear apron-looking dresses,

00:38:41.100 --> 00:38:43.480
and they are so beautiful.

00:38:43.480 --> 00:38:48.530
She must be in her 60s, but
her running down that hill

00:38:48.530 --> 00:38:53.060
and giving me the computer is
why this book is born today.

00:38:53.060 --> 00:38:57.030
I would have lost almost all my
data, everything, all images.

00:38:57.030 --> 00:39:02.260
And more than that, I would
have lost hope that I can do it.

00:39:02.260 --> 00:39:04.160
And that hope led
to another hope,

00:39:04.160 --> 00:39:06.760
and that led to another
hope, which got me here.

00:39:06.760 --> 00:39:09.670
IRFAN DAMA: That is incredible.

