I have to tell you I
spent two years in Delhi,

00:39:12.080 --> 00:39:13.830
when I worked at the
[INAUDIBLE] Sheraton.

00:39:13.830 --> 00:39:15.913
And that was when I was
first introduced to momos.

00:39:15.913 --> 00:39:18.000
I'd never heard about
momos before that.

00:39:18.000 --> 00:39:21.294
There was a small little
restaurant in chana ke puri,

00:39:21.294 --> 00:39:23.210
where all the [INAUDIBLE]
students used to go.

00:39:23.210 --> 00:39:24.430
And they would have momos.

00:39:24.430 --> 00:39:26.221
And I think the first
time, I had a thing--

00:39:26.221 --> 00:39:28.336
it had 60 momos or something.

00:39:28.336 --> 00:39:30.030
It was so good.

00:39:30.030 --> 00:39:33.502
So you have covered momos to
great degree in this book.

00:39:33.502 --> 00:39:35.210
Give us something real
quick about momos.

00:39:35.210 --> 00:39:36.464
It's such an incredible dish.

00:39:36.464 --> 00:39:38.880
VIKAS KHANNA: You know, momos
is a very interesting dough.

00:39:38.880 --> 00:39:40.130
It's a very interesting dough.

00:39:40.130 --> 00:39:43.300
It's just flour, salt and water.

00:39:43.300 --> 00:39:45.410
And then use your instinct.

00:39:45.410 --> 00:39:48.640
It needs to be a firm dough,
because if you let it rest,

00:39:48.640 --> 00:39:51.080
cover with a wet cloth
for half an hour.

00:39:51.080 --> 00:39:51.940
That's all you need.

00:39:51.940 --> 00:39:54.590
But lot of people when
I was doing any classes

00:39:54.590 --> 00:39:56.990
or doing my training of my
own chefs in the restaurant,

00:39:56.990 --> 00:39:58.920
we were worried about
the shape of the momos,

00:39:58.920 --> 00:40:01.640
you know that intricate
shape, in which we

00:40:01.640 --> 00:40:03.870
do touch a lot of that
shapes in his book.

00:40:03.870 --> 00:40:06.450
But one thing was which
is-- I tell them, tell

00:40:06.450 --> 00:40:08.960
people who cares
how the shape is.

00:40:08.960 --> 00:40:11.640
But the beauty of momos
is that you can stuff them

00:40:11.640 --> 00:40:15.550
with anything you have, any
leftovers, any restaurant

00:40:15.550 --> 00:40:16.420
food which is left.

00:40:16.420 --> 00:40:18.726
It needs to be dry for sure.

00:40:18.726 --> 00:40:20.100
And if you have
minced meat, just

00:40:20.100 --> 00:40:21.780
add some salt and
lemon juice to it.

00:40:21.780 --> 00:40:23.360
You could just stuff that in.

00:40:23.360 --> 00:40:25.640
Steaming is a great
healthy way to eat.

00:40:25.640 --> 00:40:27.530
But one more thing,
which I figured out,

00:40:27.530 --> 00:40:29.720
that you could actually
make momos with whole wheat

00:40:29.720 --> 00:40:30.860
flour too.

00:40:30.860 --> 00:40:33.120
And you can use a
lot of greens too.

00:40:33.120 --> 00:40:39.460
And this is one of my
favorite test stories about.

00:40:39.460 --> 00:40:42.370
I go to this woman's house.

00:40:42.370 --> 00:40:43.140
This is in Paro.

